      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>April 3 article about residues of pharmaceuticals and personal care products in nation's waterways misstated given name of scientist at Environmental Protection Agency; he is Christian Daughton</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article in Science Times on Tuesday about residues of pharmaceuticals and personal care products in the nation's waterways misstated the given name of a scientist at the Environmental Protection Agency. He is Christian Daughton, not Christopher.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>An article in Science Times on Tuesday about residues of pharmaceuticals and personal care products in the nation's waterways misstated the given name of a scientist at the Environmental Protection Agency. He is Christian Daughton, not Christopher.</p>
      </block>
